codex
- **Q1 CONTENT isolation: OK with caveat.** The design matches r6’s control shape: enriched appends own entities/facts to the same doc, placebo is length-matched, foreign-token, and own-entity-excluded (`dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md:51-66`; `src/python/eval/r6_index_key_enrichment.py:58-69`, `:72-84`, `:192-202`). Caveat: if alias/temporal keys are added, the design correctly requires placebo matching to the full added key set, but this is not inherited from current r6 and must be tested (`dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md:62-66`).

- **Q2 `removes_length_norm_penalty`: BLOCK.** It is mechanical, but the proposed inference is not valid enough for a gate. `b*` is chosen by argmax on the same pooled gold and then tested against `b=0.75` with an ordinary paired CI (`dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md:75-81`), so the CI ignores post-selection over the b-grid. Also, enriched@b* > enriched@0.75 does not uniquely show removal of an enrichment length penalty; it may show general BM25 `b` miscalibration. This is consistent with `probe_15b_pass` only syntactically, because the frozen function just consumes a bool (`src/python/eval/decision_rule_083.py:264-269`).

- **Q3 paired bootstrap margin-CI: OK.** The gated content quantity is the paired per-query `enriched - placebo` recall margin lower CI (`dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md:26-33`, `:69-71`), exactly what `probe_15b_pass` consumes as `enriched["margin_ci_lo"] > 0` with no raw-point gate (`src/python/eval/decision_rule_083.py:250-269`).

- **Q4 power / “at scale”: CONCERN, not block.** Using the Slice-5 power-sized LME gold is the right baseline (`dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md:67-71`; prereg `dev/design/0.8.3-mem0-parity.md:67-72`). The design also adds a paired MDE guard and underpowered⇒INCONCLUSIVE rule (`dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md:85-88`). Concern: it says “same ε-class tolerance” for an internal enriched-vs-placebo lever (`:85-86`), but ε=5pp is defined for external Mem0 near-parity (`dev/design/0.8.3-mem0-parity.md:65-72`). That may be defensible, but it is not self-evidently the smallest actionable D2 lift.

- **Q5 footprint / $0 determinism: OK with caveat.** The design explicitly pins local Qwen provenance, forbids silent fallback to priced readers, and fail-closes if unavailable (`dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md:55-61`), while measure-time is LLM-free (`:51-54`, `:112-115`). Caveat: “if cheaply derivable, the IR corpus” is a soft phrase (`:57-61`); the primary LME-only path is clear, but any IR follow-on should remain non-gating unless separately pinned.

- **Q6 misleading Slice-25 verdict: CONCERN.** The “necessary-not-sufficient” framing is mostly correct: 15b is only D2 eligibility, not 0.8.3 parity, and D2 is conditional on a remaining Mem0 gap (`dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md:35-38`; prereg `dev/design/0.8.3-mem0-parity.md:99-102`). It also acknowledges D0b accuracy≫recall and that a 15b pass may not move parity (`dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md:40-47`, `:120-122`). But the document contradicts itself on underpower: §2 says underpowered FAIL is INCONCLUSIVE (`:85-88`), while Purpose/DoD say FAIL ⇒ Slice 25 defers/drops (`:23-24`, `:115-116`). That can yield a misleading negative eligibility verdict unless the INCONCLUSIVE path overrides all “FAIL ⇒ defer” wording.
